that have been helpful for you in getting people together.

00:08:24.440 --> 00:08:27.880
Yeah, that's a very good question.

00:08:27.880 --> 00:08:38.840
And so we have the SWAT team is like 100% dedicated consultancy group.

00:08:38.840 --> 00:08:41.719
And then we have the R core team and people in that team.

00:08:42.919 --> 00:08:48.760
They can be pharmacokineticians, stat programmers, biopsychicians, but they also help with this

00:08:48.760 --> 00:08:50.440
initiative as well.

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:56.760
And then within the core team, we have multiple initiatives, which is like internal outreach,

00:08:56.760 --> 00:09:02.039
external outreach, advances in R, communication, education.

00:09:02.039 --> 00:09:09.080
So we have all those different streams that are targeting different levels of engagement

00:09:09.080 --> 00:09:09.799
within R.

00:09:10.359 --> 00:09:14.200
So for example, within, let's say internal outreach.

00:09:14.200 --> 00:09:20.359
So within internal outreach, we have the hangout sessions similar to, well, very similar to

00:09:20.359 --> 00:09:22.679
what we're doing right now, but within Pfizer.

00:09:23.559 --> 00:09:25.479
And then we have the book club.

00:09:25.479 --> 00:09:28.840
And then we have the community of practice events.

00:09:28.840 --> 00:09:35.000
It's every event that happens every month where people can come in, colleagues can come

00:09:35.000 --> 00:09:37.159
and present their various projects.

00:09:38.119 --> 00:09:42.200
And it also varies in the expertise level.

00:09:42.200 --> 00:09:46.679
Certain presentations kind of very suitable for beginners level.

00:09:46.679 --> 00:09:49.080
And then others are more complex and advanced.

00:09:49.799 --> 00:09:59.479
So targeting this, you know, approaching R and learning and bringing people together

00:09:59.479 --> 00:10:06.280
from all the different perspectives kind of helps because even if colleagues can come

00:10:06.280 --> 00:10:09.559
to hangouts this week, maybe they can attend community of practice.

00:10:09.559 --> 00:10:13.880
And at the community of practice, they would hear about hangouts and who's the guest next

00:10:13.880 --> 00:10:14.359
time.

00:10:14.359 --> 00:10:18.840
Maybe they will have time to do that next time.

00:10:18.840 --> 00:10:26.200
And then the book club is also the initiative that is very, I think we have around 140 people

00:10:26.200 --> 00:10:32.039
now all around the world, like in Philippines and Japan and U.S. and Mexico.

00:10:32.039 --> 00:10:34.919
So this was a big initiative as well.

00:10:35.479 --> 00:10:42.359
And then we have the external outreach where we track people who are part of different

00:10:42.359 --> 00:10:43.640
external working groups.

00:10:43.640 --> 00:10:47.239
And we're trying to identify the gaps in the representation.

00:10:47.239 --> 00:10:54.840
So it's if I try to answer your questions, question kind of like in short, it's targeting

00:10:55.719 --> 00:11:02.280
from kind of different sources and different angles, the community aspect of it.

00:11:04.280 --> 00:11:04.840
Thank you.

