00:46:26.939 --> 00:46:33.899
I was just going to add on to that, that after the user community meetings, we kind of save

00:46:33.899 --> 00:46:39.179
the slide decks and, you know, that becomes a showcase for what ARC can do.

00:46:40.620 --> 00:46:47.020
So that's one way of kind of having that, you know, internal place for people to see

00:46:47.020 --> 00:46:48.219
what ARC can be used for.

00:46:49.020 --> 00:46:53.659
The nice thing, again, because that's internal, you can be as specific as you like and you

00:46:53.659 --> 00:46:58.939
can, you know, talk about real kind of detail of the project you were working on and, you

00:46:58.939 --> 00:47:03.340
know, where to find resources, where to even find the code to make things happen that maybe

00:47:03.340 --> 00:47:04.699
you can't share externally.

00:47:06.219 --> 00:47:15.419
The other nice part of it is the, sorry, there was the sharing in the community side.

00:47:17.419 --> 00:47:24.219
About kind of influencing it upwards to let people know what ARC can be used for, I think

00:47:24.219 --> 00:47:30.780
it's, you need a handful of cases where you can demonstrate someone being super humanly

00:47:31.820 --> 00:47:37.500
efficient and that will get management's, you know, attention really quick.

00:47:37.500 --> 00:47:43.979
It's like you went from data to final result in how long, you know, that will garner attention

00:47:43.979 --> 00:47:44.939
like nobody's business.

00:47:45.820 --> 00:47:50.060
So, you know, that's where things like Markdown and Shiny and things like that are gateway

00:47:50.060 --> 00:47:53.580
drugs for ARC because managers will just look at that and go, that's amazing.

00:47:53.580 --> 00:47:54.939
How do you even think about doing that?

00:47:57.500 --> 00:48:03.100
I've been trying to frame our, like our customer stories in that way too, or like conference

00:48:03.100 --> 00:48:06.540
talks I see to try and put it into like two or three sentences.

00:48:06.540 --> 00:48:12.459
And one that's coming to mind right now is Tiger Tang who was on here and he said how

00:48:12.459 --> 00:48:20.060
he saved 12,000 hours with R and just like putting that number out there front and center

00:48:20.060 --> 00:48:21.179
to get people's attention.

00:48:23.419 --> 00:48:25.820
But I love all this conversation here.

00:48:25.820 --> 00:48:29.899
I feel like we could go for two hours on all of this.

